  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 8.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "He smote the Philistines.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Hezekiah's Philistine war seems to have followed on an attempt which Sargon made to bring the whole country under the Assyrian dominion. Sargon attacked Philistia in  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "date",
        "text": "B.C. 720",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", made Gaza and the other towns subject, and committed the custody of them to tributary kings, in whom he had confidence. But opposition soon manifested itself. Sargon's creatures were expelled - Akhimiti from Ash-clod, Padi from Ekron. Hezekiah assisted in this war of independence, attacked Sargon's viceroys, and helped the cities to free themselves. About the year  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "date",
        "text": "B.C. 711",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Sargon speaks of a league against Assyria, to which the parties were Philistia, Judaea, Edom, and Moab ('Eponym Canon,' p. 130). The Philistines, whom Hezekiah \"smote,\" must be regarded as Assyrian partisans, whom he chastised in the interests of the national party. He did not seek conquests in Philistia for himself. Even unto Gaza. Gaza seems to have remained faithful to Assyria from its capture in  ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "date",
        "text": "B.C. 720",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And the borders thereof, from the tower of the watchmen unto the fenced city.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (On this expression, see the comment upon ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 17:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) 2 Kings 18:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
